

1- DJVIEW4
==========

1.1 - DJVIEW4
-------------

DjView4 is a standalone DjVu document viewer built on the DjVuLibre library
and the Qt toolkit.

Highlights:
- entirely based on the public DjVuLibre API
- written in portable C++ with Qt 5 / Qt 6
- works natively under Linux/X11, Windows, and macOS
- continuous and side-by-side page scrolling
- specify a URL directly on the djview command line
- thumbnail grid and outline sidebar
- page names, metadata dialog, annotations
- built-in export (image, PDF/PS, TIFF), print support
- implemented as reusable Qt widgets

Prerequisites:
- DjVuLibreExperimental (or any DjVuLibre >= 3.5.28)
- Qt 6 (recommended) or Qt 5 >= 5.15
- CMake >= 3.21
- A C++14-capable compiler (GCC 9+, Clang 10+, MSVC 2019+)


2- BUILDING FROM SOURCE
========================


2.1 QUICK START (all platforms)
--------------------------------

Clone both repositories side by side:

  git clone https://github.com/<owner>/DjVuLibreExperimental  -b develop
  git clone https://github.com/<owner>/DjView4Experimental    -b develop

Build DjVuLibre first, then DjView4:

  # --- Linux / macOS ---
  cmake -S DjVuLibreExperimental -B djvulibre-build -G Ninja \
        -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
        -DDJVULIBRE_USE_BUNDLED_DEPS=OFF \
        -DDJVULIBRE_ENABLE_GTEST=OFF \
        -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$PWD/djvulibre-prefix
  cmake --build djvulibre-build --parallel
  cmake --install djvulibre-build

  cmake -S DjView4Experimental -B djview-build -G Ninja \
        -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
        -DDJVIEW_DJVU_INSTALL_DIR=$PWD/djvulibre-prefix
  cmake --build djview-build --parallel

  # --- Windows (PowerShell, requires VCPKG_ROOT set) ---
  cmake -S DjVuLibreExperimental -B djvulibre-build `
        -DDJVULIBRE_USE_BUNDLED_DEPS=ON `
        -DDJVULIBRE_ENABLE_GTEST=OFF
  cmake --build djvulibre-build --config Release --parallel
  cmake --install djvulibre-build --config Release --prefix djvulibre-prefix

  cmake -S DjView4Experimental -B djview-build `
        -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE="$env:VCPKG_ROOT\scripts\buildsystems\vcpkg.cmake" `
        -DVCPKG_TARGET_TRIPLET=x64-windows-release `
        -DDJVIEW_DJVU_INSTALL_DIR="$PWD\djvulibre-prefix"
  cmake --build djview-build --config Release --parallel


2.2 CMake OPTIONS
-----------------

  DJVIEW_DJVU_INSTALL_DIR   Path to a pre-built DjVuLibre install prefix.
                            If empty, CMake searches the system / vcpkg.

  DJVIEW_BUILD_TRANSLATIONS Build and install .qm translation files (ON by
                            default; requires Qt LinguistTools).

  DJVIEW_ENABLE_PLUGIN      Build with DDE/X11 viewer-protocol plugin support
                            (ON by default).

  DJVIEW_BUNDLE_DJVU_DEPS   Copy DjVuLibre runtime libs into the install tree
                            alongside djview.  Use together with CPack to
                            produce a self-contained installer.

  DJVIEW_DJVU_SOURCE_DIR    Path to the DjVuLibreExperimental source checkout
                            (used for git-describe info in the About dialog).
                            Auto-detected as ../DjVuLibreExperimental if left
                            empty.


2.3 CMake PRESETS
-----------------

Ready-made presets are defined in CMakePresets.json.  Requires VCPKG_ROOT to
be set for the Windows presets.

  cmake --preset windows-x64-release   # Release build, x64
  cmake --preset windows-x64-debug     # Debug  build, x64
  cmake --preset linux-x64-release     # Release build, Linux
  cmake --preset linux-x64-debug       # Debug  build, Linux

After configuring with a preset, build with:

  cmake --build --preset windows-x64-release


2.4 PRODUCING A SELF-CONTAINED INSTALLER (Windows)
---------------------------------------------------

The CMake build integrates with CPack to generate a NSIS installer (.exe)
and a ZIP archive that bundle djview.exe, all Qt DLLs, and the DjVuLibre
runtime DLL in a single package.

  cmake -S . -B build -DDJVIEW_BUNDLE_DJVU_DEPS=ON ...
  cmake --build build --config Release --parallel
  # Install to a staging directory first so windeployqt runs:
  cmake --install build --config Release --prefix build/_install
  cd build && cpack -G "ZIP;NSIS" -C Release

The resulting DjView4-<version>-win64.exe / .zip are in the build/ directory.


2.5 LINUX SYSTEM INSTALL
--------------------------

If DjVuLibre is already installed system-wide (libdjvulibre-dev):

  cmake -S . -B build -G Ninja -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build --parallel
  sudo cmake --install build


2.6 BUILDING ON MAC OS X
--------------------------

Install Qt 6 and DjVuLibre via Homebrew:

  brew install qt cmake ninja djvulibre

Then:

  cmake -S . -B build -G Ninja \
        -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
        -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=$(brew --prefix qt)
  cmake --build build --parallel

For a macOS app bundle, set CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET and use
-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX to place djview into an .app skeleton, then
use macdeployqt.


3- CONTINUOUS INTEGRATION
==========================

GitHub Actions workflows are in .github/workflows/:

  ci.yml        Primary CI — builds Linux x64, Linux ARM64, Windows x64,
                Windows ARM64 on every push to develop/master and on PRs.
                Produces installers on Release builds.

  ci-manual.yml Manual trigger — specify platform, build type, and a custom
                DjVuLibreExperimental ref to test against unreleased library
                branches.
